Enhance your Smart Home experience with TECKIN's products.

If you own an Alexa Echo Show, you can ask Alexa Echo Show to display the live view from your TECKIN Cam.

Follow the steps here to connect your TECKIN account to Alexa:
1. Download the "TECKIN" app from the app store;
2. Register a TECKIN account to add your devices;
3. Configure your devices and name the devices;
4. Download the "Alexa" app from the app store;
5. Configure Alexa Echo Show in the "Alexa" app;
6. Search for "TECKIN CAM" from the skills category in the "Alexa" app;
7. Enable "TECKIN CAM" skill, and you'll be navigated to TECKIN's login page;
8. Log into your TECKIN account to finish.


Once the "TECKIN CAM" Skill is enabled, simply ask Alexa to control your TECKIN devices by their names. For example:
“Alexa, show (name of device)"
“Alexa, stop"


If you experience any problems while using this skill, please contact us at support.tec@teckinhome.com
